The paper deals with security properties in key-exchange algorithms used in the TLS protocol, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The proposed mechanisms for improving forward secrecy also involve software engineering (cs.SE) and system implementation (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of mass surveillance programs on Internet traffic, which could fall under the category of cybercrime (cs.CY).
